en_847641_0	A special religious programme, organized by the ‘Ariyamagga Organization’ at the Mahaweli Maha Stupa in Kotmale on Saturday (2) was joined by the troops in the Security Force Headquarters - Central (SFHQ-Cen).
en_847641_1	Colombo-based ‘Ariyamagga Organization’ in a request to the Commander of the Army appealed to have Army personnel too joined for this meritorious act.
en_847641_2	Accordingly, 3 (V) Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR) troops under the 112 Brigade of the 11 Division under the SFHQ-Cen were enabled to take part in this meritorious programme.
en_847641_3	04 Officers and 60 Other Ranks of the 3(V) SLSR provided their fullest support to make this programme a success.
en_847641_4	During this programme, troops provided accommodation to 359 Buddhist monks and supplied alms and other facilities.
en_847641_5	Troops attended to all the needs of the programme as per directions of the Commander of the Army under the direct supervision of Major General Rukmal Dias, Commander, Security Forces - Central.
